{"data":{"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Workout Tracker (in progress)","technologies":"React, Redux (with redux-persist), TypeScript, Material-UI, HTML5, CSS3","priority":6,"slug":"workoutTracker","shortDesc":"My first real-world React app created to help with remembering my gym workouts and results.","headerImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7777777777777777,"src":"/static/c1e46780083a041958e99772766f707c/6fbf7/WorkoutTracker.png","srcSet":"/static/c1e46780083a041958e99772766f707c/a0798/WorkoutTracker.png 180w,\n/static/c1e46780083a041958e99772766f707c/83f67/WorkoutTracker.png 360w,\n/static/c1e46780083a041958e99772766f707c/6fbf7/WorkoutTracker.png 720w,\n/static/c1e46780083a041958e99772766f707c/728bb/WorkoutTracker.png 1080w,\n/static/c1e46780083a041958e99772766f707c/bdd82/WorkoutTracker.png 1184w","sizes":"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"}}}},"html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 400px;\"\n    >\n      <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 88.62115127175367%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Screenshots from app\"\n        title=\"Screenshots from app\"\n        src=\"/static/c21589eb4bda7dab3c623ff049df99d2/c7805/WorkoutTracker1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/c21589eb4bda7dab3c623ff049df99d2/c0399/WorkoutTracker1.png 100w,\n/static/c21589eb4bda7dab3c623ff049df99d2/9ec3c/WorkoutTracker1.png 200w,\n/static/c21589eb4bda7dab3c623ff049df99d2/c7805/WorkoutTracker1.png 400w,\n/static/c21589eb4bda7dab3c623ff049df99d2/34e8a/WorkoutTracker1.png 600w,\n/static/c21589eb4bda7dab3c623ff049df99d2/813d4/WorkoutTracker1.png 747w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n    </span></p>\n<p>First bigger mobile-first React app that I designed and built from scratch completely on my own. Its purpose is to log workouts. After creating a routine, it is very easy to log exercises and modify them on the fly. Features very clear interface, stores data offline on localStorage. There is still a lot to do (like drag and drop functionality, preset exercise names, confirmation dialog on removing exercise), but it is already a MVP. Deployed on Netlify.</p>\n<p><strong>Live version:</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://workouttracker.szymonpulut.com\">https://workouttracker.szymonpulut.com</a></p>\n<p><strong>GitHub repository:</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/szymonpulut/workouttracker\">https://github.com/szymonpulut/workouttracker</a></p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Personal website - portfolio","technologies":"React, Gatsby, ES6 JavaScript, GraphQL, HTML5, CSS3","priority":5,"slug":"personalWebsite","shortDesc":"Minimalistic portfolio website showcasing my projects and abilities.","headerImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7777777777777777,"src":"/static/357027c596390141a3da85c4556d6e30/6fbf7/Portfolio.png","srcSet":"/static/357027c596390141a3da85c4556d6e30/a0798/Portfolio.png 180w,\n/static/357027c596390141a3da85c4556d6e30/83f67/Portfolio.png 360w,\n/static/357027c596390141a3da85c4556d6e30/6fbf7/Portfolio.png 720w,\n/static/357027c596390141a3da85c4556d6e30/728bb/Portfolio.png 1080w,\n/static/357027c596390141a3da85c4556d6e30/91f24/Portfolio.png 1280w","sizes":"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"}}}},"html":"<p>Simple and minimalistic portfolio website to showcase my projects and abilities. Made in React &#x26; Gatsby for server-side rendering. Enforced airbnb style guide. I learned a lot about consistent styling and used global SASS mixins. Deployed on GitHub Pages.</p>\n<p><strong>Live version:</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://szymonpulut.com\">https://szymonpulut.com</a></p>\n<p><strong>GitHub repository:</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/szymonpulut/szymonpulut.github.io\">https://github.com/szymonpulut/szymonpulut.github.io</a></p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Burger Builder","technologies":"React (with Router, Redux, and axios), ES6 JavaScript, HTML5, CSS3","priority":4,"slug":"burgerBuilder","shortDesc":"Burger Builder app created during a comprehensive online React course.","headerImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7777777777777777,"src":"/static/4e512d29ab5dd17b1fc958021579fd8b/6fbf7/BurgerBuilder.png","srcSet":"/static/4e512d29ab5dd17b1fc958021579fd8b/a0798/BurgerBuilder.png 180w,\n/static/4e512d29ab5dd17b1fc958021579fd8b/83f67/BurgerBuilder.png 360w,\n/static/4e512d29ab5dd17b1fc958021579fd8b/6fbf7/BurgerBuilder.png 720w,\n/static/4e512d29ab5dd17b1fc958021579fd8b/728bb/BurgerBuilder.png 1080w,\n/static/4e512d29ab5dd17b1fc958021579fd8b/91f24/BurgerBuilder.png 1280w","sizes":"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"}}}},"html":"<p>A burger builder app i made during a course <a href=\"https://www.udemy.com/course/react-the-complete-guide-incl-redux/\">React - The Complete Guide</a> (Maximillian Schwarzmuller, udemy.com). Started with a simple app, over time built into an advanced webapp. Features authentication, Redux for global state keeping, axios for storing data in database. After \"finishing\" I added my own modifications - introduced PropTypes, changed the style of code (hooks usage, more consistent naming, performance changes, absolute imports), enforced airbnb style guide and developed a couple of new features. Deployed on Firebase.</p>\n<p><strong>Live demo:</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://burgerbuilder.szymonpulut.com\">https://burgerbuilder.szymonpulut.com</a></p>\n<p><strong>GitHub repository:</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/szymonpulut/BurgerBuilder\">https://github.com/szymonpulut/BurgerBuilder</a></p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Webpack Training Project","technologies":"Webpack, Babel, React, ES6 JavaScript","priority":3,"slug":"webpackTrainingProject","shortDesc":"A simple webpack application built along a module in online React course.","headerImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7777777777777777,"src":"/static/9fd7329a55c00c7c3414d9e777c03f62/6fbf7/Webpack_Training_Project.png","srcSet":"/static/9fd7329a55c00c7c3414d9e777c03f62/a0798/Webpack_Training_Project.png 180w,\n/static/9fd7329a55c00c7c3414d9e777c03f62/83f67/Webpack_Training_Project.png 360w,\n/static/9fd7329a55c00c7c3414d9e777c03f62/6fbf7/Webpack_Training_Project.png 720w,\n/static/9fd7329a55c00c7c3414d9e777c03f62/728bb/Webpack_Training_Project.png 1080w,\n/static/9fd7329a55c00c7c3414d9e777c03f62/91f24/Webpack_Training_Project.png 1280w","sizes":"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"}}}},"html":"<p>A basic webpack project for bundling a React app. Created following a module in an online course <a href=\"https://www.udemy.com/course/react-the-complete-guide-incl-redux/\">React - The Complete Guide (incl Hooks, React Router, Redux)</a> made by Maximilian Schwarzmüller and available on <a href=\"https://www.udemy.com/\">udemy.com</a>. Slightly developed further on my own (e.g. \"absolute\"-like imports, enforced code style).</p>\n<p><strong>GitHub repository:</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/szymonpulut/webpack_training_project\">https://github.com/szymonpulut/webpack_training_project</a></p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Node.js Training Project","technologies":"Node.js, Express.js, EJS, MongoDB, ES6 JavaScript, jQuery","priority":2,"slug":"nodejsTrainingProject","shortDesc":"A simple todo application built along an online Node.js course for beginners.","headerImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7777777777777777,"src":"/static/67e3ec50044deec54cd0dbb99b1de2b0/6fbf7/Nodejs_Training_Project.png","srcSet":"/static/67e3ec50044deec54cd0dbb99b1de2b0/a0798/Nodejs_Training_Project.png 180w,\n/static/67e3ec50044deec54cd0dbb99b1de2b0/83f67/Nodejs_Training_Project.png 360w,\n/static/67e3ec50044deec54cd0dbb99b1de2b0/6fbf7/Nodejs_Training_Project.png 720w,\n/static/67e3ec50044deec54cd0dbb99b1de2b0/728bb/Nodejs_Training_Project.png 1080w,\n/static/67e3ec50044deec54cd0dbb99b1de2b0/91f24/Nodejs_Training_Project.png 1280w","sizes":"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"}}}},"html":"<p>A basic Node.js todo app. Created following an online course <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PL4cUxeGkcC9gcy9lrvMJ75z9maRw4byYp\">Node.js tutorial for beginners</a> made by The Net Ninja and available on <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/\">youtube.com</a>. Developed on my own (e.g. code refactoring for ES6 syntax and modern jQuery) and deployed on Heroku.</p>\n<p><strong>Live demo (initial delay of ~5s due to Heroku boot up):</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"http://nodejs-todo.szymonpulut.com/\">http://nodejs-todo.szymonpulut.com/</a></p>\n<p><strong>GitHub repository:</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/szymonpulut/nodejs_training_project\">https://github.com/szymonpulut/nodejs_training_project</a></p>"}},{"node":{"frontmatter":{"title":"Tablet Dashboard legacy","technologies":"HTML5, CSS3 (grid display), JavaScript (with jQuery)","priority":1,"slug":"tabletDashboardLegacy","shortDesc":"Basic dashboard for my smart home project. Legacy because I wrote it when I didn't have much knowledge or experience in JS.","headerImage":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/png;base64,","aspectRatio":1.7777777777777777,"src":"/static/d2252040a21338565295604c183c7617/6fbf7/TabletDashboardLegacy.png","srcSet":"/static/d2252040a21338565295604c183c7617/a0798/TabletDashboardLegacy.png 180w,\n/static/d2252040a21338565295604c183c7617/83f67/TabletDashboardLegacy.png 360w,\n/static/d2252040a21338565295604c183c7617/6fbf7/TabletDashboardLegacy.png 720w,\n/static/d2252040a21338565295604c183c7617/728bb/TabletDashboardLegacy.png 1080w,\n/static/d2252040a21338565295604c183c7617/2513a/TabletDashboardLegacy.png 1440w,\n/static/d2252040a21338565295604c183c7617/ec873/TabletDashboardLegacy.png 1920w","sizes":"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"}}}},"html":"<p>Tablet Dashboard Legacy is a dashboard for my custom smart home system. Displays current time, date, weather, forecast. Connects to Google's APIs to download Google Calendar. Shows data from smart home sensors (MQTT through WebSockets). Can open main and small gate, plays an audio alert on entrance. Features automatic night and silent mode.</p>\n<p><strong>Written in legacy Javascript, when I didn't have much knowledge or experience - code is not optimal by any means (and looks ugly).</strong> Uses CSS3 grid display, ES5 JS, bits of jQuery. I plan to rewrite it as React app.</p>\n<p><strong>GitHub repository:</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/szymonpulut/TabletDashboard\">https://github.com/szymonpulut/TabletDashboard</a></p>"}}]}}}